Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.00,1:23:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,More than a question I have an\Nexperience I'd like to relate to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.52,1:23:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, it's a memory of waking up laying on\Nmy back and I was looking up to the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.60,1:23:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,ceiling and the walls had this paisley\Ngreen wallpaper and it was a window on
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.44,1:23:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the south side of the house and it was a\Npaper blind drawn down. as light was
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.00,1:23:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,streaming through this little crack and\NI was laying there just admiring this
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.44,1:23:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,dust particles and I was in the most\Nprofound bliss. I could I was happier
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.36,1:23:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,than I can't express how the joy that I\Nwas I was experiencing was a broken
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.48,1:23:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,light fixture on the ceiling and I could\Nhear my mother and a woman that I knew
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.36,1:23:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the other room along with another\Nwoman that I didn't know and I could
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.92,1:23:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,hear the tinkling of cups. I knew they\Nwere drinking coffee or tea.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.00,1:23:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the door opened\Nand an 8-year-old girl stepped in the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.23,1:23:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,room with long brown hair and a couple\Nof teeth missing and smiled and turned
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.67,1:24:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,back and told my mother, "He's awake."\NAnd then she walked over to the side of
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.04,1:24:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the bed and started playing with me and\NI was talking with her. I was
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.08,1:24:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,communicating with her and she couldn't\Nhear me. And I couldn't roll over. I
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.23,1:24:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't do anything. And I recognized\Nin that moment I thought, "That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.44,1:24:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm stepping into my existence. You\N>> hear you thought what?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.19,1:24:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I was stepping into my existence. This\Nwas a period of my birth just right
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.56,1:24:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,after my birth. I couldn't roll over. I\Ncouldn't talk. But I knew
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.96,1:24:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh,\N>> the people in the other room. I knew
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.88,1:24:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that this was my sister.\N>> Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.00,1:24:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And it fled right after that. It was\Njust it was just gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.84,1:24:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an opportunity for me and I\Npondered that many times in my life of
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.00,1:24:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of knowing of a of a pre-existence,\Nknowing of a a time before this life.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.28,1:24:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> There was another time when I was 19. I
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.52,1:24:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was in a motorcycle accident and I was\Nkilled and I was gone for a period of
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.04,1:25:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,time. had an opportunity to sit with\Nthree what I thought were individuals
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.63,1:25:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought that I was through with\Nthis opportunity on earth. This this
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.60,1:25:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,this\N>> spirits, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.15,1:25:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.56,1:25:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And I was ecstatic to be there. I could\Nfeel this again this most profound love
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.40,1:25:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,this this overwhelming joy. By the time\Nmy my definition of it was there were
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.88,1:25:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,tens of thousands of previous loved ones\Nthat had been on this earth were
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.92,1:25:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,surrounding me and and I was just\Noverwhelmed with the joy and the love of
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.04,1:25:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,being there. And they they said, "Well,\Nslow down just a minute. What do you
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.63,1:25:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,want to do?" And I said, "Well, what do\Nyou mean? I mean, I'm through with the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.96,1:25:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,thing on earth. I'm here. I'm just this\Nis what I want to do." And they said,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.36,1:25:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"Please hold on a moment." And they left\Nand they retreated. There were three in
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.36,1:25:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,originally and two returned and said,\N"Listen, we've we've just looked over
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.32,1:25:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your existence and we strongly recommend\Nthat you go back. you've accomplished a
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.76,1:25:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,great deal, but there's so much more to\Nto be accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.44,1:25:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tried to make deals with them to\Nstay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.04,1:25:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And they kind of they got a kick out of\Nit. They thought that was pretty funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.08,1:26:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They said that, you know, it doesn't\Nwork like that. Just come back. And I
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.12,1:26:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,recognized they were going to keep\Ninsisting that I come back until I make
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.23,1:26:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,my own decision to be here. And so I\Ndid.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.19,1:26:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And I wasn't very happy about it for the\Nlongest time. I felt why did I have to
